ylinder already described above Option 2 Fix a sinking office chair.";i:2;s:104:"When your chair keeps sinking this means that valve also known as a chair cylinder is no longer working.";i:3;s:81:"In order to fix it you will either have to replace the piston or get a new chair.";i:4;s:74:"Subsequently question is how do you fix an office chair that wont go down.";i:5;s:72:"If you have an office chair that wont go up or down this is the problem.";i:6;s:53:"Usually the culprit is a faulty gas cylinder or lift.";i:7;s:103:"If your office chair keeps sinking then first check if the external mechanism needs cleaning or oiling.";i:8;s:38:"Sometimes it can be as simple as that.";i:9;s:145:"If that is not the issue then you might have to replace the pneumatic cylinder or the spring that helps with the height adjustment of your chair.";i:10;s:134:"Yet another way of fixing an office chair that keeps sinking is by replacing its pneumatic cylinder as it tends to wear out over time.";i:11;s:105:"If it is the cause of your sinking office chair then you would have to get it replaced by a professional.";i:12;s:92:"DIY is usually not recommended as installing a new pneumatic cylinder can be a tedious task.";i:13;s:27:"Use a Hose Clamp Duct Tape.";i:14;s:52:"Cheap Fix Temporary Not Adjustable Not Professional.";i:15;s:87:"One of the more common DIY quick fix or hack is to use a hose clamp and some duct tape.";i:16;s:103:"This option does not actually repair the office chair but can stop your chair from temporarily sinking.";i:17;s:78:"The air pressure gets preserved and efficiently makes its work due to sealing.";i:18;s:104:"The air-tight sealing prevents the pneumatic cylinder from leaking the air pressure when you put a load.";i:19;s:93:"In short words chair sinking happens after the leakage of air pressure due to faulty sealing.";i:20;s:149:"The lever that normally lets you adjust the height activates a valve in the pneumatic piston on the stem of the chair which lets air move in and out.";i:21;s:122:"Eventually this valve will leak and your chair will just sink to the lowest position as soon as there is any weight on it.";i:22;s:73:"Changing pistons can be difficult and sometimes not possible if they are.";i:23;s:88:"This video shows a tutorial on how to fix a sinking office chair for less than a dollar.";i:24;s:34:"See more of my content and follow.";i:25;s:70:"Do you ever feel like you are sinking when you sit on your desk chair.";i:26;s:21:"This means one thing.";i:27;s:31:"Your chair is letting you down.";i:28;s:75:"Chairs that have faulty adjustable cylinders have this as a common feature.";i:29;s:56:"You see your desk chair uses a pneumaticpiston cylinder.";i:30;s:86:"This cylinder controls the height of your chair through its pressurized air operation.";i:31;s:71:"When you try and sit up straight but the chair keeps bringing you back.";i:32;s:54:"Sinking is the most common problem with office chairs.";i:33;s:94:"If your office chair keeps sinking it means that there may be an issue with your gas cylinder.";i:34;s:112:"Gas cylinders are designed to keep the seat in a fixed position and allow you to change the height of the chair.";i:35;s:54:"Thus it is the cylinder that causes the chair to sink.";i:36;s:47:"How To Fix A Computer Chair That Keeps Sinking.";i:37;s:76:"A sinking office chair does not indicate that it is bad for the whole chair.";i:38;s:77:"In reality there is also a very straightforward reason as to why this occurs.";i:39;s:47:"A workplace chairs piston also missed its lift.";i:40;s:25:"Hose Clamp And Duct Tape.";i:41;s:60:"Take apart the chair so as to expose the pneumatic cylinder.";i:42;s:47:"You will find a screw on its end or at the top.";i:43;s:84:"This screw is used to adjust the valve that let air pass in and out of the cylinder.";i:44;s:76:"Turn this screw to the either sides and see if it sinks again with pressure.";i:45;s:27:"Pneumatic cylindergas lift.";i:46;s:75:"This feature allows tallness adjustment actu